The White House,distancing itself from remarks by the administration's budgetchief, said the Federal Reserve's current course of monetarypolicy was appropriate.    "The administration feels that the current course ofmonetary policy is appropriate," White House spokesman MarlinFitwater said.    Fitzwater said the administration did not endorse remarksby White House budget chief James Miller, who said he wasconcerned the Federal Reserve might overreact to the decline inthe value of the U.S. dollar by raising interest rates. More&#3;